The paper deals with the capacity region of a multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) broadcast channel (BC) and transmission schemes for it. This falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also discusses rate-splitting (RS) and precoding techniques, which are relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Finally, the paper proposes practical algorithms, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG).
